    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Foxx Forgotten</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bill Stephney letter about Mar 25 article on stand-up comedians says Jamie Foxx was neglected (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It is an unfortunate omission to not include the work of Jamie Foxx in Caryn James's ''Out on the Tightrope, Where Comics Try Acting'' [March 25]. Mr. Foxx not only emerged as a stand-up comedian (''Def Comedy Jam''), but he also appeared in the same comic ensemble television show (''In Living Color'') that Jim Carrey did. Further, in 2005 Mr. Foxx won the best actor Oscar for his role in ''Ray'' and was nominated for best supporting actor for ''Collateral.''</p>
        <p>Bill Stephney  Randolph, N.J.</p>
      </block>
